H.7 verify (2026-05-14):

Scope: live load test proving the Phase H pipeline (SKIP LOCKED +
       lease + per-row timeout + workspace fairness + batch 100 +
       chain + rate-limit guard + EMF observability) drains 100
       synthetic rows in well under 60s.

Method: no-stub-endpoint variant — 100 composio_poll_state rows
       inserted with toolkit='loadtest' (no adapter registered),
       so the kicker's no-adapter UPDATE-backoff branch fires for
       each row. This exercises the entire SQL claim + chain path
       at scale without creating any cloud_runs, making zero
       Composio HTTP calls, and incurring ~zero AWS cost.

Constraint relaxations for the test:
  - POLL_PER_WORKSPACE_CAP raised 5 → 100 via Lambda env override
    (so the SELECT can claim all 100 rows in one workspace).
  - POLL_MAX_CALLS_PER_WORKSPACE_PER_SWEEP raised 30 → 100 (so
    H.5's rate-limit guard doesn't throttle the test rows).
  - Both reverted post-test via aws lambda
    update-function-configuration restoring the pretest env.

Test run:
