Throughput math validated:
  100 rows processed in 3.3 seconds = ~30 rows/sec wall clock.
  This is the SQL-only path (no Composio HTTP); production
  workloads spending ~300ms-3s per adapter call would scale
  more slowly — but the SQL claim + chain + lease + emit pipeline
  is provably NOT the bottleneck at 100 rows.

